introduction.p:
Let (t,x,y,z) be time and coordinates of an arbotrary event E in frame S and (t',x',y',z') in frame S' as shown in . Lorentz transformation gives the following relations for the situation in this figure.

	 \amp t = \dfrac{t' + V x/c^2}{\sqrt{1 - V^2/c^2}} 
	 \amp x = \dfrac{x' + V t}{\sqrt{1 - V^2/c^2}} 
	 \amp y = y',\ \ z = z'.

You can, of course, write the relation other way around as well.

	 \amp t' = \dfrac{t -  V x/c^2}{\sqrt{1 - V^2/c^2}} 
	 \amp x' = \dfrac{x - V t}{\sqrt{1 - V^2/c^2}} 
	 \amp y' = y,\ \ z' = z.
